HEADWORD: Deforcement
<hw>De*force"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A keeping out by force or wrong; a
wrongful withholding, as of lands or tenements, to which another has a
right.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>Resistance to an
officer in the execution of law.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

